hopobject.body: Where are you from? methylprednisolone dose dogs Clint Dempsey was wearing a giant ice pack on one leg and a smile after the Sounders' 1-0 victory over the archrival Portland Timbers. It had been a brutal game at times -- "a man's game," as Dempsey put it -- but in the end, in a match Seattle was under heavy pressure to win, the Sounders found a goal through a second-half Eddie Johnson header to delight the crowd of 67,385, the second-largest standalone attendance in MLS history.
